  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: As I scroll up to catch up on the conversation, the scroll position jumps around as new messages arrive. This is pretty annoying, especially on busy public chats.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/7532782/42754465-d8f0a768-88f4-11e8-91e8-6c148a1dab85.png\" width=\"200\">\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nScroll position does not jump when new message arrives in a chat.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nScroll position jumps as new message arrives in a chat.\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n- Join public chat with lot of messages\r\n- Scroll the public chat\r\n- Receive new messages in the chat and observe the scroll position\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: 0.9.22\r\n* Operating System: Android, iOS\r\n",
